    97	
    98	We haven't been able to locate anything remotely resembling USR firmware
    99	online. If it did exist, it would be a copy of the ROM code in the Dual
   100	Standard ROM and could not conceivably even be run on an 80x86
   101	microprocessor, much less operate as a Trojan Horse. It would be data that
   102	garage-shop pirates would use to create unauthorized copies of the ROM using
   103	an Electrically Programmable Read Only Memory (EPROM) programming device.
   104	This would be put in the Sportster to convert it to a Courier Dual Standard.
   105	This would certainly be copyright violation, and we cannot condone it in any
   106	form. But it disqualifies itself as a candidate for a Trojan Horse program
   107	quite thoroughly.
   108	
   109	The only file we can find online even remotely relating to this warning is a
   110	tiny 24KB program titled USRPATCH.ZIP. It appears to come from Johan Franzn
   111	of Twilight Garden BBS at 46-8-510-50925 (FidoNet 2:201/258). The program is
   112	apparently authored by "Jeffe and Alex" who credit Henrik Johansson with the
   113	discovery. It appears to simply send the AT command previously described to
   114	the modem from the DOS command line. In this way, you can run the program,
   115	and then your terminal program, and not have to enter the AT command at all
   116	each time you use the modem.
   117	
   118	We are thoroughly confused by U.S. Robotics' warning. And any attempt to talk
   119	to anyone within the company leads to a lot of finger pointing and referral
   120	to other telephone numbers in an essentially endless fashion. First, the
   121	program does nothing more than send the AT commands to the modem and U.S.
   122	Robotics "copyright" to AT commands of any sort is openly questionable.
   123	Secondly, there is nothing we can find wrong with this file, and the question
   124	of a Trojan Horse program appears to be blatantly transparent fear mongering
   125	of the worst sort. In fact, the concept of a software program causing
   126	"irreparable damage to a hard drive mechanism is ludicrous. The most virulent
   127	viruses and most damaging Trojan Horse programs can only damage data on hard
   128	disk drives - not the hard disk drives themselves. This is officially and
   129	totally utter nonsense. It was undoubtedly drafted by a lawyer to the ongoing
   130	chagrin and mortified embarrassment of every technical person within this
   131	fine company.
   132	
   133	We understand their distress. And we'll shed no tears for anyone running
   134	garage shop EPROM mills that might be prosecuted. But technically ridiculous
   135	warning messages do nothing but call into question the credibility of USR
   136	itself. Trying to "scare" users into NOT entering simple commands to make the
   137	modem they bought and paid for more capable doesn't even make sense from a
   138	marketing standpoint. And lost in the confusion is the fact that their "Radio
   139	Shack Intercomm" model is actually a dynamite little modem on its own merits,
   140	at a reasonable price. That a few of the early buyers of this modem got a
   141	good deal, can only work to U.S. Robotics benefit - if they don't work too
   142	hard to turn it into a negative.
